  the first attempt to cure type  diabetes by pancreas transplantation was done at the university of minnesota in minneapolis on december  … this opened the door to a period between the mids to mids where only segmental pancreatic grafts were used in the late s – early s three major events… boosted the development of pancreas transplantation… at the spitzingsee meetings participants had the idea to renew the urinary drainage technique of the exocrine secretion of the pancreatic graft with segmental graft and eventually with whole pancreaticoduodenal transplant that was clinically achieved during the mids and remained the mainstay technique during the next decade in parallel the swedish group developed the whole pancreas transplantation technique with enteric diversion it was the onset of the whole pancreas reign the enthusiasm for the technique was rather moderated in its early phase due to the rapid development of liver transplantation and the need for sharing vascular structures between both organs liver and pancreas during the modern era of immunosuppression the whole pancreas transplantation technique with enteric diversion became the gold standard… for spk pak pta cs maint uses authors parameter link    angela cullen eva von schaper  fresenius agrees to buy app for up to  billion bloomberg news archived from the original on  retrieved    the discovers on the key patents were np desai soonshiong pa sandford mw grinstaff and ks suslick adding k s wong to the two  patents see further readingcitation needed  crowe deborah  october  celgene closes abraxis acquisition los angeles business journal retrieved  october  subscription required  company overview of nanthealth llc bloomberg businessweek  february  retrieved  february    shawn baldwin september   dr patrick soon shiong generates billions of value creation in medicine fast company   dolan brian sep   soonshiong’s big rollup gets a name nantworks retrieved  january    mcbride ryan  october  biotech billionaire’